> This cooking technique not only looks impressive on the plate, it also makes for a super crispy and delicious dish that's perfect for sharing with friends.

Preheat the oven to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Carefully cut widthway slices into each @baby potatoes{500%grams} at 3mm intervals. Don't cut all the way through.

Pop the potatoes on a lined #baking tray{}. Spread out in a single layer.

Drizzle with @oil{to taste} and season with @salt{to taste}, @pepper{to taste} and half the @paprika{2%sachets}.

Roast on the top shelf until golden and tender, ~{25-35%minutes}. With ~{5%minutes} left to cook, scatter the @grated cheese{50%grams} over the potatoes and return to the oven to melt the cheese.

Meanwhile, finely chop the @chives{5%grams}(finely chopped) (use scissors if you prefer).

Add the remaining paprika, @creme fraiche{110%grams}, @chipotle paste{1%sachet} and chives to a #small bowl{}.

Mix to combine then season to taste with salt and pepper.

When ready, pop the cheesy hasselbacks onto a #sharing plate{}.

Serve the chive and chipotle sauce alongside for dipping.